---
import ApiCopyButton from "../components/ApiCopyButton.astro";
import ApiPanel from "../components/ApiPanel.astro";
import { CURL_DISPLAY } from "../model.ts";

const markdown = `# API Reference

Local \`/v1\` for evidence-backed media understanding. Live translate guesses; this studies the media first, then returns receipts your pipeline can verify.

## Successful path

1. Register or list a source — /api/sources/
2. Plan or start a bounded study, poll its journal — /api/runtime/
3. Reopen evidence — /api/audits/ — or apply private captions/language explanations
4. Misses route through /api/improve/; they do not score themselves

An empty list envelope is an honest answer, not an error.

## First verified call

With a running host and bearer token, \`GET /v1/source-sessions\` proves authorization and shows registered sources.

\`\`\`bash
${CURL_DISPLAY}
\`\`\`
`;
---

<header class="api-hero">
  <div class="api-page-header-row">
    <h1>API Reference</h1>
    <ApiCopyButton kind="page" label="Copy page" ariaLabel="Copy page as Markdown" />
  </div>
  <p class="api-lede">
    Local <code>/v1</code> for evidence-backed media understanding. Live translate guesses; this
    studies the media first, then returns receipts your pipeline can verify. Studio and agentic
    editors are both clients of the same host.
  </p>
  <script is:inline type="application/json" data-api-copy-source set:html={JSON.stringify(markdown)} />
</header>

<section class="api-section" aria-labelledby="api-path-heading">
  <h2 id="api-path-heading">Successful Path</h2>
  <ol class="api-steps">
    <li>
      Register or list a source under
      <a href="/api/sources/">Sources And Ingest</a>.
    </li>
    <li>
      Plan or start one bounded study, then poll its journal under
      <a href="/api/runtime/">Runtime Lifecycle</a>.
    </li>
    <li>
      Reopen evidence under <a href="/api/audits/">Evidence Audits</a>, or apply private
      <a href="/api/captions/">Captions And QC</a> and
      <a href="/api/language/">Language Explanations</a>.
    </li>
    <li>
      Misses route through the <a href="/api/improve/">Improve</a> conveyor; they do not score
      themselves.
    </li>
  </ol>
  <p>
    An empty list envelope is an honest answer, not an error. Fail-closed reads stay unavailable or
    withheld instead of inventing output.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="api-section" aria-labelledby="api-first-call-heading">
  <h2 id="api-first-call-heading">First Verified Call</h2>
  <div class="api-split">
    <div>
      <p>
        With a running host and bearer token, <code>GET /v1/source-sessions</code> proves
        authorization and shows what is already registered. Then move to Runtime Lifecycle for the
        study itself.
      </p>
      <p>
        Host on loopback; bearer required. See
        <a href="/api/authentication/">Authentication</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="api-panels">
      <ApiPanel title="First Call" body={CURL_DISPLAY} />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
